Given I'm logged-in with valid credentials
When I select 'Female' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'MRI pelvic floor' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
Then I go to Page 03 and select 'Yes' in Contrast enhanced
When I select 'Sequences' box
Then I select 'DWI' from Weighting dropdown
Then I go to Page 08 of Pelvic MRI
And I click on 'Finding' radio button
And dropdown below 'Finding' is enabled

When I select 'Sigma mass' from the dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is preselected

And 'Upper third' checkbox is enabled
And 'Middle third' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lower third' checkbox is enabled

And 'Size*' input field is enabled
And '2nd plane' input field is enabled
And '3rd plane' input field is enabled

And 'Circumscribed' radio button is enabled
And 'Non-circumscribed' radio button is enabled

And 'Nodular' radio button is enabled
And 'Multinodular' radio button is enabled

And 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

And 'Focal wall thickening' checkbox is enabled
And 'Conglomerate' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tumour necrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Mesenteric fat stranding' checkbox is enabled

And 'Strong' radio button is enabled
And 'Low' radio button is enabled
And 'No' radio button is enabled

And 'Diffusion restriction' checkbox is enabled

When I enter '1' in the input field 'Size*'
Then the number is accepted
When I enter '9999' in the input field 'Size*'
Then the number is accepted

When I enter '1' in the input field '2nd plane'
Then the number is accepted
When I enter '9999' in the input field '2nd plane'
Then the number is accepted

When I enter '1' in the input field '3rd plane'
Then the number is accepted
When I enter '9999' in the input field '2nd plane'
Then the number is accepted

When I select 'Strong' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Low' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

